Product description

No Wiring Needed & Add the Wall Switch

Remote Light Switch Kit

Remotely turn on/off ceiling lights, plug-in pendants, standing floor lamps, tabletop lamps, and hard-to-reach lights with a push of a wall switch.

Adds approximately 1.97'' in height or length

The compact size is more convenient to install and will not affect the overall shape of your lamps.

NOTE: Please measure the size carefully before you buy if you want to use it under lampshade or in tight space.

      Excellent!!! Perfect for older homes with old fashioned pull-string lights with no wall switch!
      With this adapter, you don't need to call an electrician to wire a wall switch for a ceiling light. Just use your existing fixture (or upgrade to a non-string-pull fixture), screw the bulb into this adapter and you're ready to go! You can mount the switch on your wall, or anywhere handy, or use it hand-held! You can get rid of your old fixture's pull-string (just make sure to turn the fixture ON first). Now your light turns on and off (and is even dimmable with a dimmable bulb) at the touch of a finger on the modern, wireless wall switch. This is also excellent for remotely switching table and floor lamps on and off from a room entryway, instead of tripping in the dark to reach the lamp. This is excellent for safety for elderly or disabled individuals. Just make sure your lamp or fixture has enough room inside to accommodate the added dimensions of the adapter, as it won't fit in every fixture with the bulb. Also, it's possible that a smaller bulb could be used for your application to make it work.
      I am very pleased with this excellent product!

      Range is flaky--proving <1m, in this case
      Reviewed in the United States on June 18, 2023
      Style: Remote Control
      I purchased this to replace a 9V battery powered wireless light switch that I previously had mounted, with blu-tak, on the wall directly opposite a 4m wide kitchen from the desired light. This switch, even after following provided instructions for pairing switch with light... See more
      I purchased this to replace a 9V battery powered wireless light switch that I previously had mounted, with blu-tak, on the wall directly opposite a 4m wide kitchen from the desired light. This switch, even after following provided instructions for pairing switch with light socket, would not turn the light off from that distance. On, yes; but not off.

      I moved the switch mounting plate to the side of the refrigerator, less than a meter from the light, and much less convenient than beside the door from which we enter the room, where it had been, previously. I found, there, that the switch plate will NOT magnetically adhere to the side of the refrigerator, because the magnets are in the hand-held switch itself, and not in the plate, which only has a couple steel ingots, loosely stuck in place with brittle, fragile glue--dropping one ingot the moment I first moved the switch away from the plate. This might not be an issue, except that the switch *still* won't fully function without me pulling it out of its plate.

      Mounted barely a meter from the light, it refuses to turn the light off (consenting only to on), unless I remove the switch from the plate and hold it a few cm from the light.

      The watch battery in the switch arrived with a plastic card in place, to keep it disconnected, so I have to assume it had a fresh and full charge. But it fails at what I would have expected would be a rather simple job, given the operative range mentioned in the description (100m).

      I'm glad the switch was relatively inexpensive, but it sucks to have to buy yet another one, and search for a more reliable brand, when virtually all varieties of this product, on Amazon, come from hitherto unknown manufacturers, named with barely pronounceable dipthongs and clumsy consonant blends.

      I should have known better. UPDATED
      Reviewed in Canada on April 20, 2023
      Below is my original review which received 1 star. Dewenwils contacted me through Amazon after I posted the review below. As you'd expect from a decent seller, they wanted to make it right. After I completed some troubleshooting at their request, they decided the base... See more
      Below is my original review which received 1 star. Dewenwils contacted me through Amazon after I posted the review below. As you'd expect from a decent seller, they wanted to make it right. After I completed some troubleshooting at their request, they decided the base was working but the remote was faulty. They sent me (directly) a replacement set at no cost. The replacement works as described by the manufacturer. It's ideal for my purposes and as Dewenwils said in a previous email to me, this new switch set does not cause interference with another Dewenwils remote switch I have in close proximity. All in all between the email exchanges I had with their customer relations to address my questions and the troubleshooting, I received the replacement set in about a week. l'm happy they contacted me and made the effort to address a faulty product that somehow got passed their quality control process, assuming they have one. Thank you Dewenwils. Original review follows... This is not the first time I purchased this product and had problems. The current issue with my most recent purchase is that the switch turns the closet light on, however it does not turn the light off. This version has the magnetic/removable remote feature allowing you to 'unhook' the hand held remote from the wall mounted face plate. That's the only saving grace here because I have to hold the remote within a few inches of the socket in order to switch the closet light off. Where I have it wall mounted is no more than 36 inches from the base/socket. So why it turns it ON but not OFF is a complete mystery. There is a little red indicator light on the remote unit which flashes rapidly whenever you use the remote. I assume this is an indicator telling you the remote is transmitting to the socket. This red light flashes the same regardless if I'm tapping the ON or OFF portion of the switch. I've reprogrammed the switch by following the instructions provided with the product but still, it fails to turn the light off unless I hold the remote right next to the base. I started this review by stating this is not the first time I purchased this product. Previously I had problems where this switch would activate other lights I have in my house. Other lights that I didn't want activated. When I contacted Dewenwils they denied responsibility saying that the problem was caused by interference with other Dewenwils switches because their pre-programmed channels were the same. Dewenwils said the only fix was to return the unit to Amazon and hope that the replacement that Amazon sends would be a programmed to a different channel. Really? That's Dewenwils business model? Fool me once shame on you. Fool me twice shame on me. Thus my review title... I really should have known better.
